FBIS3-29718 "dreas035_l_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-035 Document Type:Daily Report 22 Feb 1994 Philippines Officials Burn Illegal Casette, Video Tapes BK2102131794 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network in Tagalog 0930 GMT 21 Feb 94 BK2102131794 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network in Tagalog 0930 GMT 21 Feb 94 Language: Tagalog Article Type:BFN [Text] Confiscated illegal cassette and video tapes and other fake products were burned in Pasig earlier today. The ceremony was attended by representatives from the Videogram Regulatory Board [VRB] and Committee on Intellectual Property Rights. According to Trade Secretary Rizalino Navarro, their campaign against groups copying products with patents, copyrights, and trademarks will not stop. Meanwhile, VRB Chairman Javier Carbonell said that they will continue to conduct raids on video shops selling or renting illegal tapes. VRB raided video shops in Greenhills and Pasig in Manila the other week.
